CC peripheral
Peripheral type:
pinout

API
pinsConnected()
Returns a table showing which pins are currently connected to common.
local states = p.pinsConnected()
print(states[1]) -- true/false
print(states[9]) -- always true
Pin 9 always reports as connected because it is the common/reference terminal.

connectPin(pinOrTable)
Connects one or more pins to common.
p.connectPin(1)
p.connectPin({2, 3, 4})
Only pins 1–8 can be contolled.

disconnectPin(pinOrTable)
Disconnects one or more pins from common.
p.disconnectPin(1)
p.disconnectPin({2, 3, 4})
Again, only pins 1–8 can be controlled.

comparePin(pin)
Returns the voltage difference between the given pin and pin 9/common.
print(p.comparePin(1))
This is equivalent to:
print(p.comparePin(1, 9))

comparePin(pin, referencePin)
Returns the voltage difference between two pins.
print(p.comparePin(1, 5))
This returns:
voltage(pin 1) - voltage(pin 5)

pinsVoltage()
Returns a table of all pin voltages relative to pin 9/common.
local volts = p.pinsVoltage()
print(volts[1])
print(volts[2])

pinsVoltage(referencePin)
Returns a table of all pin voltages relative to another pin.
local volts = p.pinsVoltage(1)
print(volts[9])
